title.narrative: Relevant MDAs, select LGAs, schools and communities have increased capacities to ensure inclusive access and completion of basic education, especially for the most vulnerable children and adolescents, in a safe and protective environment

description.narrative: Against a backdrop of an approved National Inclusive Education Strategy addressing factors of exclusion from schools, an Integrated- Programme- for- Out of School Adolescents is now launched with enrolment of 9,939 (4,675 male, 5,264 female) out-of-school adolescents, being equipped with skills. Additionally, national guidelines (including a National Guidance, Counselling and Child Protection Guide for schools and teachers' colleges) and strategies supporting improvements in equity and inclusiveness in education are now available. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:12/11/2019
